<div id="review_1741188057" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1741188057" />
    <a title="Regina Lindsey" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6693237-regina-lindsey"><img alt="Regina Lindsey" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1348604150p2/6693237.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1741188057?book_show_action=true">Aug 28, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Regina Lindsey" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Regina Lindsey" href="/user/show/6693237-regina-lindsey">Regina Lindsey</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780719560095" href="/book/show/823815.A_Golden_Age">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6693237-regina-lindsey?shelf=civil-war">civil-war</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6693237-regina-lindsey?shelf=women-authors">women-authors</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6693237-regina-lindsey?shelf=complex-woman">complex-woman</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6693237-regina-lindsey?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6693237-regina-lindsey?shelf=cultural">cultural</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6693237-regina-lindsey?shelf=family-relationships">family-relationships</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6693237-regina-lindsey?shelf=favorite">favorite</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6693237-regina-lindsey?shelf=war-fiction">war-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6693237-regina-lindsey?shelf=female-author">female-author</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6693237-regina-lindsey?shelf=love-story">love-story</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1741188057" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13672512345999639090">Set against the backdrop of the Bangladesh Liberation War, Rehana Haque self-worth is predicated on the well-being of her son and daughter, whom she lost for a brief time when her husband died suddenly. She will do and sacrifice anything for their happiness. When the Pakistani military junta launched its attack on its citizens both children become active in the resistance movement, pulling Rehana into its intrigue as well.<br/><br/>I have to admit the I was unmoved by the first half of the book and though</span>
  <span id="freeText13672512345999639090" style="display:none">Set against the backdrop of the Bangladesh Liberation War, Rehana Haque self-worth is predicated on the well-being of her son and daughter, whom she lost for a brief time when her husband died suddenly. She will do and sacrifice anything for their happiness. When the Pakistani military junta launched its attack on its citizens both children become active in the resistance movement, pulling Rehana into its intrigue as well.<br /><br />I have to admit the I was unmoved by the first half of the book and thought the ultimate rating would be a 3. But somewhere around the half-way point there was a shift; it became impossible to put down and established itself as remarkable. By the end, even though the characters may not have been full fleshed out, Anam kicks you in the gut with a split-second choice Haque must make. The strength of the book is in its themes, mainly what we will do in the name of love - parental, romantic, and in the name of friendship. <br /><br />This is a great read for people who love a strong female protagonist and enjoy historical fiction but have a low threshold for descriptive narration of the brutality of war. Had the first half been as strong as the second half I would probably rate it a 5. But, since this is Anam's debut novel I'm hoping in the second book of the series the weaknesses have been remedied. I'm certainly anxious to see and have already downloaded <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/11331177.The_Good_Muslim" title="The Good Muslim by Tahmima Anam" rel="nofollow noopener">The Good Muslim</a></span>
  <a data-text-id="13672512345999639090" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


